summary: What a time to be a fan of GoT
body:
What a time to be a fan of GoT

So, I’ve seen the nervous breakdown of Jonærys stans on Reddit and seriously i had a good laugh. Where are all those books readers that were claiming that everything is about Dæny and that Arya and her would be braiding hair and be sisters when G.R.R Martin himself wrote “You may be as different as the sun and the moon, but the same blood flows through both your hearts. You need her, as she needs you…” Referring to Sansa and Arya’s relationship? Siblings don’t always get along…. But WHEN they do …. Oooooh boy …. And To be honest I was ready for the Jonærys promotion even a Targcest boat sex magic baby … HELL i was prepared for them to rule the 7K in the series because THAT sells (apparently..?) but now? I feel so good for my starklings i don’t even care if they won’t give us Jonsa (my deepest , darkest desire 😅)

question: Is there a possibility for j/d/s love triangle? I hate the idea but see some hints. And this shit is exactly what d&d like.
answer:
It’s possible. I went from thinking Jonsa could never ever happen to maybe it’ll happen. If it’s meant to happen, D&D would definitely go for a love triangle. If doesn’t and Dark Dany is still happening then Sansa will Dany’s strongest opposer which will force Jon to make a decision between his girlfriend or family.

Or we’re wrong and Sansa comes to love Dany and braids her hair every day.

summary: To be honest, Jon probably understands what Daenerys could do to the North if he didn’t bend the knee. Not that she would, but...
body:
To be honest, Jon probably understands what Daenerys could do to the North if he didn’t bend the knee. Not that she would, but she could.

Once he saw the fire puppies in action, there was no going back. He doesn’t want Daenerys as an enemy and he knows the North better not want her as an enemy.

It doesn’t diminish his love for her, but he’s not bending the knee for pussy. He did it because she’s their best chance for survival, and because after this Great War, his people don’t need another war they can’t win. There is absolutely no other option for him because what’s the point of surviving the AOTD only to be annihilated by Daenerys as soon as it’s over?

I just try to keep in mind what I said before: these actors in large part haven’t bothered to understand the story and the complex relationships as a whole. They learn what they need to in order to do their work, but they probably don’t care that much about understanding the overall story they’ve helped to tell.

And I hope Jon Snow’s dick is having a wonderful time inside Dany’s vagina mouth or wherever else she lets him put it.

summary: it’s funny to me the way ppl think d*ny is going to be THE hero who saves westeros from the NK and the threat of the WW never...
question: it’s funny to me the way ppl think d*ny is going to be THE hero who saves westeros from the NK and the threat of the WW never mind the fact that she refused to help the north unless Jon bends the knee (a true hero would put the safety of the people she wants to rule before her own greedy needs, winning their love and trust by helping them, not by taking their lands by force) or the fact that she didn’t give a flying fuck about the threat until she lost one of her dragons. (1/3)
answer:
and despite all that people think SHE is going to be the savior. these ppl really think Jon came back from the dead just to give d*ny a baby lizard, also fuck Bran’s entire arc! , his only job is to tell Dany that Jon is her family! all the sufferings he went through and all that power he gained isn’t important at all. anyway I’m almost confident that if another dragon dies or if she discovers cersei’s betrayal (2/3)

she’s gonna leave everybody behind and go after cersei for revenge because she CAN’T accept defeat, her battle (if u even call it a battle that was more like a massacre) with the lannister army was a major proof of that. she really burned the food out of SPITE bc she didn’t want cersei to have it! she didn’t even stop to think for a second to think about keeping the food for her army at least! no way that girl will stick around and help ppl if she lost. (3/3)

They put so much stock on the ability of the dragons that no amount of undercutting will change their minds. The Night King killed Viserion like it was a regular lizard instead of a powerful dragon and Dany stans think the other dragons will be instrumental if only they learnt to zig zag. The Night King rose a dragon from the dead, if fire was such a destructive force for him and dragons are fire made flesh, it shouldn’t have happened. We spent 7 seasons with Dany where her focus was solely on the Iron Throne, yet her stans who applaud her ambition, determination and one track mindedness think she’ll put everything she has on the line to save humanity when the entire point of the truce was so that Dany doesn’t lose anything to Cersei while she in the North. That’s how important the Iron Throne is to Dany. Ensuring that Cersei sits tight in King’s Landing doing nothing that might benefit her was a thing Dany needed before she could help the North like she promised. There was a line about Astapor falling in the show, most people missed it but Dany did nothing for them. She left the Bay of Dragons in shambles to the least qualified person she could find and went for the one thing she wanted most of all. Despite this history, she’s apparently the Saviour.

We spent 7 seasons with Dany where her focus was solely on the Iron Throne, yet her stans who applaud her ambition, determination and one track mindedness think she’ll put everything she has on the line to save humanity when the entire point of the truce was so that Dany doesn’t lose anything to Cersei while she in the North. That’s how important the Iron Throne is to Dany. Ensuring that Cersei sits tight in King’s Landing doing nothing that might benefit her was a thing Dany needed before she could help the North like she promised. There was a line about Astapor falling in the show, most people missed it but Dany did nothing for them. She left the Bay of Dragons in shambles to the least qualified person she could find and went for the one thing she wanted most of all. Despite this history, she’s apparently the Saviour.

summary: Crone Talk We’re a couple weeks away from the season finale of Game of Thrones and a lot’s been said and will be said and I want...
body:
Crone Talk

We’re a couple weeks away from the season finale of Game of Thrones and a lot’s been said and will be said and I want in on the fun. I’ve loved it since 2011 when I saw the second season on TV. I picked up the A Game of Thrones from the book store and the rest is history.

I always wanted to write about Thrones and I finally have time. I’m deciding still whether it’ll be a series of posts but for sure, I’ll geek out about the new episodes. For now, theories, predictions, and spoilers should suffice. And yes, that is a young Richard Madden. Robb Stark 4ever hoes

First off, I want to talk about the final season but before that we gotta contextualize. A lot of the latter seasons of GoT feel ham-fisted and the writing had been choppy at best, terrible at worst (battle of the—sorry, loot train? wight hunt?). A lot of the books’ plot lines were merged like Sansa and fakeArya, Ellaria Sand and Arianne Martell. I sympathise with anyone who started hating the show when it veered away from the books. A lot of the great exposition, subtle plotting, and Martin’s masterful writing were gone. His universe is ever expanding like our own and it’s beautiful but it is, at the end of the day, a TV show with time and budget(lol) constraints and insane logistics to consider.

And to the show writers’ credit, it was always going to be tough. Remember that George told D&D the broad strokes of the endgame at the beginning. Show writers had to get everyone (no less than twenty mostly three-dimensional fully fleshed out characters, mind you) into final positions (physically and emotionally) within season 5-7 (maybe 6-7) for the endgame, which is already written, at least the outline is.

Sidenote: Theres a seperate argument here about the screenwriting but I’m not going into that. I wanted to show big picture look at GoT as it kicks into high gear.

Also, I recall D&D wanting 3 big budget movies but HBO wanted to keep the series format so instead we have six 15 million dollar episodes (fun reminder here that LOTR is actually six books in uh, three). So I doubt there’ll be minor problems like the pacing issues like last season and hopefully less poorly named battles. Given this, I have higher expectations for the upcoming final season. They’ve literally been building up everything to this big ‘holy shit’ season. In another post, I’ll be talking about the wars to come. Til then.
